964
01:13:00,327 --> 01:13:04,593
Oh, sure, you look exactly like
that guy in Rain Man.

965
01:13:06,934 --> 01:13:09,767
Oh, yeah? Well, people say
I look like Tom Cruise all the time.

966
01:13:09,870 --> 01:13:11,565
Oh, yeah? No, I'd, uh...

967
01:13:12,673 --> 01:13:16,336
The other one, the... What's his...
Uhhh... The retard.

968
01:13:17,344 --> 01:13:22,577
I just love that scene in Vegas
when the retard wins at blackjack.

969
01:13:23,517 --> 01:13:25,451
You look just like that.

970
01:13:29,323 --> 01:13:36,195
What I could never understand, though,
is how someone so retarded,

971
01:13:37,097 --> 01:13:38,792
could win so much.

972
01:13:41,168 --> 01:13:44,660
Hey, Jeffrey, his brother
from another mother,

973
01:13:44,772 --> 01:13:46,535
how did that retard
win so much?

974
01:13:46,640 --> 01:13:49,575
- You know what, sir? I think that maybe...
- Okay, get your hands off me.

975
01:13:49,676 --> 01:13:51,871
Oh, I didn't mean it.

976
01:14:26,080 --> 01:14:29,277
His luck'll run out eventually.
It always does.

977
01:14:39,660 --> 01:14:41,890
- Hey, Ben...
- No, Ben, stop it!

978
01:14:41,995 --> 01:14:43,860
- What the hell is the matter with you?
- Hey, come on! Ben!

979
01:14:43,964 --> 01:14:47,422
Oh, you think that's funny?
You think that was funny? Shut up!

980
01:14:47,534 --> 01:14:48,899
I understand, Ben.
We don't need any more...

981
01:14:49,002 --> 01:14:50,833
This is not the time. Okay?

982
01:14:50,938 --> 01:14:53,240
I wanna thank you for
confirming my choice in Ben.

983
01:14:53,240 --> 01:14:54,776
- Sure.
- Now, go home.

984
01:15:01,582 --> 01:15:03,573
- What?
- You're off the team.

985
01:15:03,684 --> 01:15:04,742
No.

986
01:15:05,752 --> 01:15:09,119
- I was-I was drunk, I was...
- I don't care what you were.

987
01:15:10,357 --> 01:15:11,654
I'm not leaving.

988
01:15:11,758 --> 01:15:14,283
Yes, you are.

989
01:15:14,795 --> 01:15:17,263
What are you gonna do
about it, huh?

990
01:15:21,135 --> 01:15:25,003
You've been the big man for a long time,
but you just acted like a child.

991
01:15:25,105 --> 01:15:28,233
So, I want you to pick up
the ticket and go home,

992
01:15:28,342 --> 01:15:32,369
because if you don't, you know exactly
what I'm capable of doing,

993
01:15:32,980 --> 01:15:34,277
don't you?

994
01:15:51,532 --> 01:15:52,521
All right, listen up.

995
01:15:52,633 --> 01:15:56,160
Casino's gonna change out their chips,
just like the MGM did after the Tyson fight.

996
01:15:56,270 --> 01:15:59,137
That means we got less
than 24 hours to cash in,

997
01:15:59,239 --> 01:16:01,503
or we're gonna be sitting with
200 grand of worthless plastic.

998
01:16:01,608 --> 01:16:03,838
- So, we'll cash out.
- It's too hot.

999
01:16:03,944 --> 01:16:07,846
They're gonna be dissecting the eye in
the sky footage of Fisher's little power play.

1000
01:16:07,948 --> 01:16:10,143
So, let's do it right now
before they can do that.

1001
01:16:10,250 --> 01:16:12,218
Are you deliberately slow?

1002
01:16:13,053 --> 01:16:14,611
What about them?

1003
01:16:15,989 --> 01:16:17,547
What about them?

1004
01:16:17,658 --> 01:16:21,958
They can cash in the chips.
The casino's just gonna think they're tips.

1005
01:16:29,403 --> 01:16:30,836
- Cashing out.
- Thank you.

1006
01:16:30,938 --> 01:16:33,031
- Thank you.
- Thanks, sweetie.

1007
01:16:33,640 --> 01:16:36,074
- Thanks, hon.
- Thank you, baby.

1008
01:16:40,747 --> 01:16:42,806
I love a parade,
don't you?

1009
01:16:43,984 --> 01:16:47,750
You know, there's a word
I don't throw around all that often,

1010
01:16:48,355 --> 01:16:49,583
"Genius".

1011
01:17:18,085 --> 01:17:21,111
Hey, Kianna. Let me hold
your bag for a second.

1012
01:17:21,822 --> 01:17:23,084
Thanks, baby, here.

1013
01:17:23,190 --> 01:17:24,680
Oh, no problem. Anytime.

1014
01:17:24,791 --> 01:17:27,692
- Watch. Watch, watch. Ready?
- Okay, I'm watching. That's beautiful.

1015
01:17:27,794 --> 01:17:28,783
Watch.

1016
01:17:28,895 --> 01:17:32,626
No, it's great, you just need a little, uh,
to get your knee a little higher.

1017
01:17:54,788 --> 01:17:56,312
- Hi.
- Hey.

1018
01:17:57,691 --> 01:18:00,125
So, the Hard Rock
comped me a suite.

1019
01:18:01,361 --> 01:18:03,329
That's cool, that's great.

1020
01:18:06,400 --> 01:18:08,095
You wanna see it?

1021
01:19:10,464 --> 01:19:13,126
All right, take care, Bobby.
All right?

1022
01:19:33,620 --> 01:19:35,144
God, it's cold.

1023
01:19:35,589 --> 01:19:37,489
Hey, what time is it?

1024
01:19:38,458 --> 01:19:41,621
He's only 45 minutes late.
Show a little patience.

1025
01:19:43,029 --> 01:19:45,088
Oh, look.
Here he comes.

1026
01:19:45,899 --> 01:19:47,890
Guys, I'm sorry I'm late.

1027
01:19:48,001 --> 01:19:49,229
Hey, Ben.

1028
01:19:49,503 --> 01:19:51,300
You know, you could try
returning a call once in a while.

1029
01:19:51,405 --> 01:19:53,566
Good of you to show up, man.
It's not like we're cold or anything.

1030
01:19:53,673 --> 01:19:55,038
Yeah, funny.

1031
01:19:56,343 --> 01:19:59,972
- Hey, did you bring it?
- Yeah, I got it. There it is.

1032
01:20:00,080 --> 01:20:03,015
And you're sure you didn't inlay
the software on more space

1033
01:20:03,116 --> 01:20:04,310
than the parameters suggest?

1034
01:20:04,418 --> 01:20:06,443
No. It's just one-fifth
of the free face.

1035
01:20:06,553 --> 01:20:08,544
Let's fire this mother up.

1036
01:20:08,655 --> 01:20:09,917
Beautiful.

1037
01:20:18,765 --> 01:20:19,993
Okay.

1038
01:20:20,534 --> 01:20:21,626
Okay.

1039
01:20:25,138 --> 01:20:26,730
What's happening?

1040
01:20:30,076 --> 01:20:32,601
- I don't understand.
- It's the wrong size.

1041
01:20:32,712 --> 01:20:33,974
No. What?

1042
01:20:35,048 --> 01:20:38,347
- What the hell, Ben? This is an 8K.
- Right.

1043
01:20:40,020 --> 01:20:41,920
Yeah, we needed 16K!

1044
01:20:43,356 --> 01:20:47,156
I can't believe this.
- I-I thought it was an-an 8K.

1045
01:20:47,260 --> 01:20:48,852
- No, you didn't.
- Yeah, I did.

1046
01:20:48,962 --> 01:20:53,194
No, you didn't. You knew the entire
time the discrete was 16K.

1047
01:20:53,700 --> 01:20:54,962
Damn it, Ben.

1048
01:20:55,068 --> 01:20:58,333
It's gonna take us two weeks
to get a fresh 16K from the fabrication.

1049
01:20:58,438 --> 01:21:01,839
And another five days, minimum,
to get it ready to press.

1050
01:21:01,942 --> 01:21:05,378
Miles, calm down, all right?
It was, uh, an honest mistake.

1051
01:21:08,014 --> 01:21:09,311
What?

1052
01:21:11,651 --> 01:21:16,418
You know what? Um, I think we're gonna
have to go at this without you, man.

1053
01:21:17,524 --> 01:21:19,219
You-you're gonna what?

1054
01:21:22,062 --> 01:21:25,657
No, no. This is just
as much mine as it is yours.

1055
01:21:25,765 --> 01:21:28,359
We've been working on this
for over a year.

1056
01:21:28,468 --> 01:21:32,029
I know that. But your heart
just isn't in this anymore.

1057
01:21:37,811 --> 01:21:39,369
You serious?

1058
01:21:46,086 --> 01:21:47,110
Fine.

1059
01:21:48,955 --> 01:21:50,047
Fine.

1060
01:21:51,458 --> 01:21:55,690
You know what? I don't even care.
Honestly, I don't even care.

1061
01:21:55,795 --> 01:21:57,023
You know why?

1062
01:21:57,130 --> 01:22:01,499
'Cause no one in the real world gives
a shit about the 2.09 Competition.

1063
01:22:02,602 --> 01:22:04,467
You know, it's just something
that you build up in your head

1064
01:22:04,571 --> 01:22:06,562
to make yourselves
feel important.

1065
01:22:06,673 --> 01:22:08,573
You guys are pathetic.

1066
01:22:08,675 --> 01:22:09,835
Thanks.

1067
01:22:16,816 --> 01:22:18,215
Welcome back, Mr. Youngman.

1068
01:22:18,318 --> 01:22:22,084
- Thanks, Joseph. It's good to see you.
- Good to see you, too.

1069
01:22:25,725 --> 01:22:28,717
Good evening, Mr. Youngman,
welcome back to the Red Rock.

1070
01:22:28,828 --> 01:22:30,295
Nice to see you.

1071
01:22:30,397 --> 01:22:33,059
Anything I can do for you,
let me know.

1072
01:22:50,617 --> 01:22:51,982
Double down.

1073
01:23:27,721 --> 01:23:30,747
I guess you play big
or you don't play at all.

1074
01:23:31,958 --> 01:23:33,186
Right?

1075
01:23:35,695 --> 01:23:39,722
Honey, there you are. Let's go.
We don't wanna miss the show!

1076
01:23:39,833 --> 01:23:42,631
Honey, we're actually
playing a game here.

1077
01:23:43,103 --> 01:23:44,195
Yeah.

1078
01:23:44,604 --> 01:23:46,367
Yeah, so,
you know what?

1079
01:23:46,473 --> 01:23:50,534
Why don't you run upstairs
and, uh, wait for me there? Okay?

1080
01:23:53,146 --> 01:23:54,977
All right. Let's go.

1081
01:24:00,153 --> 01:24:02,144
Yeah, all right.

1082
01:24:02,756 --> 01:24:05,350
I've got the worst
headache right now.

1083
01:24:19,372 --> 01:24:21,203
- Ten.
- Come on, monkey.

1084
01:24:21,307 --> 01:24:23,673
- Fourteen.
- Come on. Come on, monkey.

1085
01:24:23,777 --> 01:24:25,904
- Sixteen.
- Monkey. Come on.

1086
01:24:27,213 --> 01:24:28,646
Twenty-one.

1087
01:24:35,088 --> 01:24:37,022
Pete, you're killing us.

1088
01:24:50,270 --> 01:24:52,261
I guess it's not my night.

1089
01:25:17,067 --> 01:25:19,277
Are you out of your mind?

1090
01:25:19,943 --> 01:25:22,725
I, uh, I don't know
what happened.

1091
01:25:23,002 --> 01:25:25,630
I-I messed up.
I'm sorry.

1092
01:25:26,011 --> 01:25:28,034
Oh, oh, you're sorry.

1093
01:25:28,141 --> 01:25:31,736
Oh, see, now that's what I've been waiting
to hear, Ben. As long as you're sorry.

1094
01:25:31,845 --> 01:25:36,407
I'm out 200 grand, but Ben's sorry!
Everybody hear that? Ben's sorry!

1095
01:25:36,516 --> 01:25:40,577
So, we can all go back to being
friends and laughing over cocktails!

1096
01:25:41,788 --> 01:25:43,153
Come on, Micky.
It can happen to anyone.

1097
01:25:43,256 --> 01:25:44,689
They get on a rush
and they lose control.

1098
01:25:44,791 --> 01:25:46,418
You shut your mouth.
This is business.

1099
01:25:46,526 --> 01:25:49,893
Hey, I let you down,
all right? I get it.

1100
01:25:49,996 --> 01:25:53,830
Excuse me? You let me down?
I don't care!

1101
01:25:54,467 --> 01:25:57,595
Let me make one thing clear to you,
I am not your father!

1102
01:25:57,704 --> 01:26:00,730
You are not my friend.
This is a business.

1103
01:26:01,007 --> 01:26:03,134
You are only as good to me
as the money you make,

1104
01:26:03,243 --> 01:26:04,938
and, right now, it's not
worth a hell of a lot!

1105
01:26:05,044 --> 01:26:06,525
You're gonna give me back
everything you lost.

1106
01:26:06,525 --> 01:26:09,644
No, no, no! I can't do that!
That money was for Harvard!

1107
01:26:09,749 --> 01:26:11,649
I have made you so much more
than what I just lost!

1108
01:26:11,751 --> 01:26:13,582
It doesn't matter, Ben.

1109
01:26:13,686 --> 01:26:16,814
You had very clear instructions,
and you didn't follow them.

1110
01:26:16,923 --> 01:26:20,859
You didn't do your job.
You weren't counting, you were gambling!

1111
01:26:23,396 --> 01:26:26,233
Well, why aren't you
out there, then, Micky? Hmm?

1112
01:26:26,866 --> 01:26:31,565
I mean, we take all the risks.
Seems to me like you don't do shit.

1113
01:26:36,276 --> 01:26:38,210
This isn't about me,

1114
01:26:39,045 --> 01:26:42,742
you arrogant little infant.

1115
01:26:55,662 --> 01:26:58,290
You can all find your own way
back to Boston.

1116
01:26:58,398 --> 01:27:02,459
And, Ben, you're gonna pay me that money,
every penny, one way or the other.

1117
01:27:02,569 --> 01:27:04,560
And you damn well
know it.

1118
01:27:14,647 --> 01:27:16,137
I need a drink.

1119
01:27:18,985 --> 01:27:20,418
Anybody else?

1120
01:27:23,456 --> 01:27:25,185
Yeah, well,
we don't need him.

1121
01:27:25,291 --> 01:27:26,952
- Yeah, okay, Ben.
- No, I'm serious.

1122
01:27:27,060 --> 01:27:29,722
Why do we need him?
We have our own money now.

1123
01:27:29,829 --> 01:27:33,094
You know, his cut was 50%,
and he doesn't even play!

1124
01:27:33,666 --> 01:27:34,826
Why do we need him?

1125
01:27:34,934 --> 01:27:36,026
Hey, you know what I think?

1126
01:27:36,135 --> 01:27:39,468
I think we play out the weekend,
and I think we do this without him.

1127
01:27:39,572 --> 01:27:40,971
No. No, I don't think
that's a good idea.

1128
01:27:41,074 --> 01:27:43,304
I think we should go back
to Boston and figure this out.

1129
01:27:43,409 --> 01:27:45,206
Yeah, well, why don't we
let the team decide?

1130
01:27:45,311 --> 01:27:48,439
I'm with Jill. This is Micky's thing.
Micky brought us together.

1131
01:27:48,548 --> 01:27:50,539
And then he drove us apart.

1132
01:27:50,650 --> 01:27:53,676
I mean, you saw how
he played Fisher against me.

1133
01:27:54,621 --> 01:27:58,250
Choi, what do you say, man?
You wanna make some money?

1134
01:27:59,759 --> 01:28:01,420
- Kind of.
- Really?

1135
01:28:02,195 --> 01:28:05,460
We need 100 grand just to play.
You're talking about risking our own money.

1136
01:28:05,565 --> 01:28:07,062
All I'm saying is
that we try it.

1137
01:28:08,014 --> 01:28:12,635
You know, if... we make the investment,
then we take all of the winnings.

1138
01:28:13,706 --> 01:28:15,003
All of it.

1139
01:28:22,148 --> 01:28:23,445
Okay.

1140
01:28:27,754 --> 01:28:28,812
Yeah.

1141
01:28:29,289 --> 01:28:31,348
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

1142
01:28:33,092 --> 01:28:34,286
Choi?

1143
01:28:35,662 --> 01:28:36,924
I'm in.

1144
01:28:38,798 --> 01:28:40,493
Now I need a drink.

1145
01:28:46,472 --> 01:28:48,235
- What are you doing?
- What?

1146
01:28:48,341 --> 01:28:50,309
What are you doing?

1147
01:28:50,410 --> 01:28:52,469
Well, we're printing money.

1148
01:28:52,912 --> 01:28:55,608
What, you think just 'cause Micky
left we're gonna stop?

1149
01:28:55,715 --> 01:28:58,513
No, I could do this.
I can lead this team.

1150
01:28:58,885 --> 01:29:02,150
You know, I'm not the same guy
I was back in Boston.

1151
01:29:02,622 --> 01:29:04,852
- Exactly.
- Yeah, exactly.

1152
01:29:05,358 --> 01:29:07,986
You know, isn't this exactly
who you wanted me to be

1153
01:29:08,094 --> 01:29:11,086
when you first came into
the store to buy a tie?

1154
01:29:15,368 --> 01:29:18,607
What happened to
"300,000 dollars and I'm out"? Hmm?

1155
01:29:18,972 --> 01:29:21,668
What happened to
"A means to an end"?

1156
01:29:22,608 --> 01:29:25,441
How much do you have?
- What?

1157
01:29:25,545 --> 01:29:27,740
- How much do you have?
- I got enough.

1158
01:29:27,847 --> 01:29:30,077
Come on, Ben. How much do you
have saved back in Boston?

1159
01:29:30,183 --> 01:29:32,708
I've got 315 grand,
all right?

1160
01:29:33,086 --> 01:29:35,384
Then why are you still here?

1161
01:29:36,723 --> 01:29:40,682
Because I wanna still be here.
I like being here.

1162
01:29:41,127 --> 01:29:42,992
So does everybody else.

1163
01:29:43,396 --> 01:29:46,092
So, come on, Jill.
Are you in?

1164
01:29:51,971 --> 01:29:54,735
You are the big player, Ben.

1165
01:29:54,841 --> 01:29:56,206
Yes, I am.

1166
01:29:58,644 --> 01:30:00,544
Yeah, can I get a drink?

1167
01:30:28,474 --> 01:30:30,408
Rose, I wanna thank you.

1168
01:30:31,444 --> 01:30:33,810
You have been
most accommodating.

1169
01:30:34,380 --> 01:30:36,348
All right, that's for you.

1170
01:30:36,649 --> 01:30:38,947
Okay, take care.
Hey, good luck.

1171
01:30:46,526 --> 01:30:48,517
Hey, how we doing here, people?

1172
01:30:59,839 --> 01:31:03,240
Yeah, I'm gonna put you on hold
while I track him down.

1173
01:31:06,846 --> 01:31:08,973
Just got an interesting call.

1174
01:31:11,084 --> 01:31:15,145
There's nobody left to fire us.
Planet Hollywood is our last client.

1175
01:31:17,590 --> 01:31:19,490
I don't know about that.

1176
01:31:25,131 --> 01:31:26,564
This is Cole.

1177
01:31:36,112 --> 01:31:40,141
Ahh, queen of diamonds.
Your lady luck tonight.

1178
01:31:40,646 --> 01:31:42,273
You're doing good.

1179
01:31:42,582 --> 01:31:44,345
You're a real winner.

1180
01:31:49,122 --> 01:31:51,818
Sometimes.
Just like everybody else.

1181
01:31:52,892 --> 01:31:55,087
Now, why don't I believe that?

1182
01:31:57,196 --> 01:31:59,255
Maybe you're just smarter
than everybody else, huh?

1183
01:31:59,365 --> 01:32:02,027
Yeah, I bet it's been
that way your entire life.

1184
01:32:02,135 --> 01:32:05,901
Except it just recently started
paying dividends, am I right?

1185
01:32:07,640 --> 01:32:09,005
I'd split them.

1186
01:32:09,108 --> 01:32:13,545
Deck's heavy as hell and since
I've been here, the true count's at plus 7.

1187
01:32:20,353 --> 01:32:22,446
Kianna. I think we have
a serious problem over there.

1188
01:32:22,555 --> 01:32:24,022
- Walk now!
- Oh, shit. Oh, shit!

1189
01:32:24,123 --> 01:32:27,183
Let's go. I'm out. Thank you.
Let's go, Jill. Let's go.

1190
01:32:27,293 --> 01:32:29,022
I think we need to call
security or something.

1191
01:32:29,128 --> 01:32:32,723
Yeah, I don't think they're gonna help.
Let's go! Come on.

1192
01:32:37,336 --> 01:32:39,304
Let's take a walk, huh?

1193
01:32:40,039 --> 01:32:43,805
Come on, kid. See if we can't
get you that chicken dinner.

1194
01:32:48,981 --> 01:32:51,575
It's called, uh,
biometrics.

1195
01:32:51,684 --> 01:32:55,916
Biometrics. It's sort of like,
uh, a fingerprint of your face.

1196
01:32:58,558 --> 01:33:03,791
See, when the player sits down at
the table, the software, it reads this, uh...

1197
01:33:03,896 --> 01:33:05,363
Biometric profile.

1198
01:33:05,464 --> 01:33:07,227
... biometric profile
of your face,

1199
01:33:07,333 --> 01:33:10,359
cross-references it
with a database of counters.

1200
01:33:13,906 --> 01:33:18,707
Software'll probably put you and me
out of business, but it still can't do this.

1201
01:33:21,881 --> 01:33:23,178
All right.

1202
01:33:27,323 --> 01:33:31,621
Ohh! You understand
all this. You go to MIT.

1203
01:33:31,991 --> 01:33:33,390
Smart boy.

1204
01:33:34,860 --> 01:33:36,794
My name is Cole Williams.

1205
01:33:37,396 --> 01:33:40,661
And if I ever see you
in this town again,

1206
01:33:41,434 --> 01:33:44,835
I will break your cheek bone
with a small hammer,

1207
01:33:46,072 --> 01:33:48,063
and then I will kill you.

1208
01:33:52,745 --> 01:33:56,306
Please. Please,
just take the money.

1209
01:33:57,550 --> 01:33:59,074
You can take it.

1210
01:34:01,787 --> 01:34:03,118
Tell me, uh,

1211
01:34:03,689 --> 01:34:08,422
how's... good old
Professor Rosa doing, huh?

1212
01:34:10,096 --> 01:34:14,692
Oh, yeah. Me and Micky,
we go way back.

1213
01:34:15,801 --> 01:34:18,793
I spent years, chased him
all over this town.

1214
01:34:19,238 --> 01:34:24,198
Giving him beat downs left and right,
only to find him at the tables a week later.

1215
01:34:24,310 --> 01:34:26,278
He was very persistent.

1216
01:34:27,179 --> 01:34:30,478
And then, one September night,

1217
01:34:30,983 --> 01:34:33,884
when I was in Barstow
at my father's funeral,

1218
01:34:34,754 --> 01:34:38,190
my casino was taken
for seven figures.

1219
01:34:38,291 --> 01:34:39,622
Can you imagine that?

1220
01:34:39,725 --> 01:34:42,956
The most ever taken by
a single counter in one night.

1221
01:34:43,062 --> 01:34:47,658
'Course I was, naturally,
unceremoniously fired.

1222
01:34:50,369 --> 01:34:52,132
Funny thing, though.

1223
01:34:52,538 --> 01:34:55,063
I never saw Micky Rosa
after that.

1224
01:34:56,242 --> 01:34:57,368
Never.

1225
01:36:24,096 --> 01:36:26,223
Cauchy was the first
to make a rigorous study

1226
01:36:26,332 --> 01:36:30,359
of the conditions for convergence
of an infinite series.

1227
01:36:30,469 --> 01:36:32,767
And was concerned with developing

1228
01:36:32,872 --> 01:36:37,741
the basic theorems of the calculus
as rigorously as possible.

1229
01:36:39,145 --> 01:36:40,578
Any questions?

1230
01:36:40,980 --> 01:36:43,107
No? All right, moving on.

1231
01:36:44,150 --> 01:36:48,143
Isn't it true Cauchy
stole from his students?

1232
01:36:53,058 --> 01:36:56,926
Yes, I heard that.
What's your theory on that?

1233
01:36:57,963 --> 01:37:02,491
They say he used his students
for their brilliance,

1234
01:37:03,636 --> 01:37:07,868
then discredited them
and stole their equations,

1235
01:37:09,942 --> 01:37:11,807
stole their hard work.

1236
01:37:14,513 --> 01:37:17,209
Well, that wouldn't be the first time
a teacher was accused of that.

1237
01:37:17,316 --> 01:37:22,015
I think what he's referring to
is Vladimir Stupnitsky, yes?

1238
01:37:22,121 --> 01:37:25,056
He was a student of Cauchy's
who accused Cauchy

1239
01:37:25,157 --> 01:37:28,490
of stealing his four-volume text
on this analysis

1240
01:37:28,594 --> 01:37:31,062
and publishing it
under a pseudonym.

1241
01:37:32,898 --> 01:37:34,559
Of course, nobody knows
what really went down there.

1242
01:37:34,667 --> 01:37:38,660
They never did prove it, and without
the proof, it's a little like it never happened.

1243
01:37:38,771 --> 01:37:40,796
And, you know,
it's a real shame,

1244
01:37:40,906 --> 01:37:45,104
because if Stupnitsky had just realized
that he shouldn't have crossed Cauchy,

1245
01:37:45,211 --> 01:37:46,940
this was the dispute,

1246
01:37:47,980 --> 01:37:53,976
if he'd been able to... get beyond some
of the personal mistakes that were made,

1247
01:37:54,520 --> 01:37:57,751
I have no doubt that Cauchy
would have worked with him again,

1248
01:37:57,857 --> 01:38:00,883
and they could have
done great things together.

1249
01:38:01,293 --> 01:38:05,354
But, as history shows us,
some students never learn.

1250
01:38:07,066 --> 01:38:08,727
You should get
that eye looked at.

1251
01:38:45,938 --> 01:38:47,337
You okay?

1252
01:38:50,309 --> 01:38:51,936
Everything's gone.

1253
01:38:53,746 --> 01:38:56,340
- What?
- Micky's taken everything.

1254
01:38:56,448 --> 01:39:00,680
He's taken the money,
taken away Harvard Med, even MIT.

1255
01:39:02,555 --> 01:39:04,648
- What are you talking about?
- Micky, he's taken everything.

1256
01:39:04,757 --> 01:39:07,157
I-I-I gotta find a way
to get it back.

1257
01:39:08,460 --> 01:39:09,950
Are you insane?

1258
01:39:10,563 --> 01:39:14,124
You just got the shit kicked out
of you and you won't let this go!

1259
01:39:14,233 --> 01:39:18,169
Look, what am I supposed to do, Jill?
I've just lost everything!

1260
01:39:18,938 --> 01:39:20,428
Look, please...

1261
01:39:22,241 --> 01:39:24,505
I don't wanna lose you, too.

1262
01:39:27,513 --> 01:39:31,108
Ben, you were
dragged away in Vegas.

1263
01:39:31,784 --> 01:39:36,118
I haven't heard from you.
I had no idea where you were.

1264
01:39:36,822 --> 01:39:38,050
I know.

1265
01:39:39,024 --> 01:39:40,184
I know.

1266
01:39:47,533 --> 01:39:50,331
You know, I'm so sorry
that I hurt you.

1267
01:39:52,137 --> 01:39:53,502
I'm sorry.

1268
01:39:56,375 --> 01:40:00,869
In Vegas, I don't know
what happened. That wasn't me.

1269
01:40:02,081 --> 01:40:03,708
Look, you know me.

1270
01:40:04,416 --> 01:40:06,281
You know what I'm like.

1271
01:40:08,087 --> 01:40:09,577
You know me.

1272
01:40:16,028 --> 01:40:17,893
I need you to trust me.

1273
01:40:19,231 --> 01:40:22,598
<i>And the winner of this year's 2.09</i>

1274
01:40:22,701 --> 01:40:28,970
<i>for excellence in the field of robotics
goes to the team of Connolly and Kazazi!</i>

1275
01:41:06,345 --> 01:41:09,314
That's it. That's...
that's the story.

1276
01:41:11,817 --> 01:41:14,047
Jill Taylor. Really?

1277
01:41:14,853 --> 01:41:18,345
- Yeah. Yeah, really.
- Wow.

1278
01:41:18,457 --> 01:41:22,655
Yeah, it doesn't feel like "wow," Miles.
I really screwed up.

1279
01:41:22,761 --> 01:41:27,494
Yeah, you did.
But... you had a life experience.

1280
01:41:31,937 --> 01:41:33,928
I-I can't believe
how I treated you, Miles.

1281
01:41:34,039 --> 01:41:37,941
You know, you're my best friend,
and I... really let you down.

1282
01:41:38,811 --> 01:41:41,905
I really let you down.
I'm sorry.

1283
01:41:43,716 --> 01:41:48,244
And I'm-I'm happy for you, you know?
Winning the 2.09? That's... that's great.

1284
01:41:49,621 --> 01:41:52,089
- Jill Taylor, really?!
- Yeah.

1285
01:41:54,626 --> 01:41:56,719
So, let me get
this straight.

1286
01:41:57,396 --> 01:42:00,559
Money, girls,

1287
01:42:01,734 --> 01:42:06,137
high-roller suites,
clubs, Vegas.

1288
01:42:07,339 --> 01:42:12,367
Yeah, I think I probably would have
blown off the 2.09 Competition, too.

1289
01:42:15,914 --> 01:42:17,279
So, we cool?

1290
01:42:18,917 --> 01:42:20,509
Yeah, we're cool.

1291
01:42:21,019 --> 01:42:23,715
But you better believe that you're
gonna make this up to me big time.

1292
01:42:23,822 --> 01:42:25,084
All right.

1293
01:42:26,391 --> 01:42:28,518
So, what are you
gonna do now?

1294
01:43:19,311 --> 01:43:21,142
What do you want, Ben?
This is an alumni dinner.

1295
01:43:21,246 --> 01:43:23,612
You need a diploma
to come to one of these.

1296
01:43:23,715 --> 01:43:26,115
Wait. Stupnitsky wants back in.

1297
01:43:32,324 --> 01:43:33,291
What?

1298
01:43:33,392 --> 01:43:37,522
Look, I... I've... I've had some time
to think about what you said.

1299
01:43:39,398 --> 01:43:40,888
I want back in.

1300
01:43:41,867 --> 01:43:45,735
- Why now?
- Because I have nothing else.

1301
01:43:47,606 --> 01:43:50,803
All right, look, Ben. I'm not gonna lie to you.
You're good, you're very, very good.

1302
01:43:50,909 --> 01:43:55,073
But you did exactly what I told you not to.
You got emotional and then you got stupid.

1303
01:43:55,180 --> 01:43:58,877
Now you tell me why in the world
I'd ever get back in business with you.

1304
01:43:58,984 --> 01:44:03,444
Look, I know I should never have
disrespected you, all right? I know that.

1305
01:44:04,423 --> 01:44:06,391
With this facial
recognition software,

1306
01:44:06,491 --> 01:44:09,688
our window of opportunity
is closing in on us.

1307
01:44:10,229 --> 01:44:13,892
Now, I need this, Micky.
I really, really need this.

1308
01:44:13,999 --> 01:44:19,130
Well, the take would have to be really, really
good to get me even vaguely interested.

1309
01:44:20,639 --> 01:44:25,941
Well, you know, that's... that's why I was
thinking maybe you should be the other big player.

1310
01:44:27,346 --> 01:44:30,679
You know,
two big players playing big?

1311
01:44:31,850 --> 01:44:35,183
Hey, slow down,
I haven't played in a long time, Ben.

1312
01:44:39,625 --> 01:44:41,217
But Fisher's out.

1313
01:44:42,094 --> 01:44:46,463
No one else on the team
can... be the big player, can they?

1314
01:44:49,701 --> 01:44:53,102
And if we do well,
if we do really well,

1315
01:44:53,872 --> 01:44:57,035
then you get your grades back,
get to Harvard Med,

1316
01:44:58,043 --> 01:45:00,568
and I might even
get that sabbatical.

1317
01:45:01,580 --> 01:45:06,040
Well, amazing things can be done
from the inside, right?

1318
01:45:07,986 --> 01:45:10,682
Just went back to
the head of the class.

1319
01:45:11,957 --> 01:45:13,822
I gotta go be social.

1320
01:45:19,197 --> 01:45:22,496
All right, now listen.
It's different out there this time.

1321
01:45:22,601 --> 01:45:25,468
The stakes are high
and it's more dangerous.

1322
01:45:26,004 --> 01:45:29,064
But the return...
is gonna be the biggest.

1323
01:45:30,375 --> 01:45:33,811
Now, they know our faces,
so we're gonna wear disguises.

1324
01:45:34,046 --> 01:45:36,014
And we can't mess around.

1325
01:45:36,381 --> 01:45:37,848
I'm glad you're
back with us, Micky.

1326
01:45:37,950 --> 01:45:39,850
Well, I couldn't let you guys
come back to this town

1327
01:45:39,952 --> 01:45:43,444
and not prove to Ben that
I can do more than just teach.

1328
01:45:44,289 --> 01:45:48,191
But as we've all said, this game
is about the past and the future,

1329
01:45:48,293 --> 01:45:51,353
and tonight
we forget about the past.

1330
01:45:51,596 --> 01:45:53,461
We just focus on the future.

1331
01:45:53,565 --> 01:45:56,898
Right. This is our last time.

1332
01:45:57,302 --> 01:46:00,328
Now, we all know the drill if things get ugly.
We meet at the Fox Strip Club.

1333
01:46:00,439 --> 01:46:02,771
Nobody leaves this town alone.

1334
01:46:06,244 --> 01:46:08,144
Let's go make a killing.

1335
01:46:08,680 --> 01:46:10,045
All right.

1336
01:46:32,170 --> 01:46:34,638
Let's see what we can do with this.

1337
01:46:43,749 --> 01:46:47,810
Seems like I'm having one of those days,
you know what I mean, Jim?

1338
01:46:49,488 --> 01:46:51,615
I'm bringing all the luck today.
I'm just bringing it all.

1339
01:46:51,723 --> 01:46:56,183
Anyone who's in any kind of contact
with me is getting so much luck today.

1340
01:47:07,839 --> 01:47:10,000
Winner, winner,
chicken dinner! There it is.

1341
01:47:10,108 --> 01:47:13,544
Thank you. God, I love this town.
I love this game.

1342
01:47:14,346 --> 01:47:17,645
And, Jim, I might
even love you.

1343
01:47:27,459 --> 01:47:29,654
Hey, you mind if I sit down?

1344
01:47:43,675 --> 01:47:44,733
What's your name?

1345
01:47:44,843 --> 01:47:47,971
Shane? I'm about to change your luck.
It's gonna become mine.

1346
01:47:48,080 --> 01:47:50,310
There you go,
give me it all.

1347
01:48:00,358 --> 01:48:01,552
There you go.

1348
01:48:04,329 --> 01:48:06,092
Thank you. Thank you.

1349
01:48:10,836 --> 01:48:13,066
Such a shame, Shane!

1350
01:48:14,039 --> 01:48:16,098
Okay, I'm supposed to double, right?

1351
01:48:16,208 --> 01:48:20,542
- Is this your first time, darling?
- I've been winning and losing for hours.

1352
01:48:20,645 --> 01:48:22,738
Well, that's all right.
I've been winning and losing for years.

1353
01:48:36,061 --> 01:48:37,585
What the hell kind of streak
are you on, boy?

1354
01:48:37,696 --> 01:48:40,358
This never happens,
this never happens.

1355
01:48:53,411 --> 01:48:55,208
I'm just gonna have to split those tens.

1356
01:48:55,313 --> 01:48:56,871
- Splitting tens.
- Splitting tens!

1357
01:48:56,982 --> 01:48:58,116
- Split tens!
- Again!

1358
01:48:58,116 --> 01:48:58,844
- Split tens!
- Again!

1359
01:49:21,773 --> 01:49:24,742
- Thank you, ma'am.
- Give me the chips, Blanca.

1360
01:49:25,977 --> 01:49:27,842
Give me the chips!
Come on, give me the chips, Blanca.

1361
01:49:27,946 --> 01:49:30,847
Come on,
just give me the chips!

1362
01:49:30,949 --> 01:49:35,079
- My bus has to leave right away.
- I gotta walk my dog.

1363
01:49:35,187 --> 01:49:37,747
- I'm sorry we're making such a mess.
- Go, go, go, go, go.

1364
01:49:37,856 --> 01:49:40,916
Nice to see you.
Have a good night, darling.

1365
01:49:46,464 --> 01:49:47,761
This way!

1366
01:49:58,977 --> 01:50:00,069
Go.

1367
01:50:14,426 --> 01:50:15,791
This way!

1368
01:50:21,700 --> 01:50:23,691
Come on, Jill.
Come on!

1369
01:50:33,612 --> 01:50:36,206
Go that way. Throw me the chips.
Come on, we gotta separate.

1370
01:50:36,314 --> 01:50:39,181
Give me the chips,
I'll meet you at Fox's.

1371
01:50:45,257 --> 01:50:46,849
Go, go, go, go!

1372
01:50:57,802 --> 01:50:59,463
Come on, come on.

1373
01:51:02,574 --> 01:51:04,132
Move, move, move!

1374
01:51:08,313 --> 01:51:09,575
Come on.

1375
01:51:10,715 --> 01:51:12,307
Go, go, this way.

1376
01:51:24,296 --> 01:51:26,127
All right, let's go.

1377
01:51:34,205 --> 01:51:36,696
Go, go, go, go!
Airport!

1378
01:51:55,260 --> 01:51:56,887
<i>I never saw Micky Rosa
after that.</i>

1379
01:52:01,966 --> 01:52:03,228
Oh, God.

1380
01:52:04,336 --> 01:52:06,600
But I think
I wanna see him now.

1381
01:52:07,672 --> 01:52:10,140
And I want you
to make that happen.

1382
01:52:14,412 --> 01:52:16,846
I-I don't work
for Micky anymore.

1383
01:52:19,851 --> 01:52:21,284
Come on, kid.

1384
01:52:23,121 --> 01:52:26,887
Your picture's all over the database.
Your Vegas gig is done.

1385
01:52:27,926 --> 01:52:29,860
But I will give you
one night.

1386
01:52:29,961 --> 01:52:33,021
And I can guarantee
that you won't be bothered.

1387
01:52:33,932 --> 01:52:37,698
You'll make a killing,
and you'll keep it all.

1388
01:52:40,772 --> 01:52:41,966
Listen.

1389
01:52:43,541 --> 01:52:45,008
My name's Cole.

1390
01:52:46,578 --> 01:52:48,102
Cole Williams.

1391
01:52:50,014 --> 01:52:52,414
You just bring me
Micky Rosa, kid.

1392
01:52:52,717 --> 01:52:54,742
I'll take care of the rest.

1393
01:52:57,288 --> 01:53:00,223
Son of a bitch.

1394
01:53:42,867 --> 01:53:44,630
Who the hell are you?

1395
01:54:07,492 --> 01:54:10,655
Ben. Good job.

1396
01:54:11,729 --> 01:54:16,792
You'll be glad to know I'm gonna have a talk
with your professor, and that MIT thing?

1397
01:54:17,001 --> 01:54:19,094
It's gonna
work out for you.

1398
01:54:20,672 --> 01:54:22,230
So, that's it?

1399
01:54:23,675 --> 01:54:26,439
- That's it.
- All right.

1400
01:54:27,412 --> 01:54:29,107
Oh, dr. Campbell?

