01:54:30,448 --> 01:54:33,417
They don't have pensions
in my line of work.

1402
01:54:33,751 --> 01:54:35,651
And the software does
what it's supposed to do.

1403
01:54:35,753 --> 01:54:39,655
And I been chasing Micky Rosa
around here for too damn long.

1404
01:54:40,892 --> 01:54:43,156
I'm looking at
some retirement.

1405
01:54:45,063 --> 01:54:46,530
Leave the bag.

1406
01:54:48,600 --> 01:54:50,898
No. No, no, no, no.

1407
01:54:51,002 --> 01:54:55,496
I need this money. You have no idea
what I went through to get this money.

1408
01:54:55,607 --> 01:55:00,601
I know, kid, but you're gonna figure out
how to get everything you want in this life,

1409
01:55:00,712 --> 01:55:02,441
'cause you're smart.

1410
01:55:04,015 --> 01:55:08,543
So, you're gonna
leave the bag.

1411
01:55:13,591 --> 01:55:18,187
Ben, give him the bag. Give him the bag.
It doesn't matter. Give him the bag.

1412
01:55:27,038 --> 01:55:28,835
I knew you were smart.

1413
01:55:47,692 --> 01:55:50,422
<i>I had a 1590 on my SAT.</i>

1414
01:55:50,528 --> 01:55:52,587
<i>I got a 44 on my MCATs.</i>

1415
01:55:53,097 --> 01:55:56,225
<i>And I have
a 4.0 GPA from MIT.</i>

1416
01:55:56,334 --> 01:55:58,802
<i>I thought I had
my life mapped out.</i>

1417
01:56:00,705 --> 01:56:01,797
<i>But then I remembered</i>

1418
01:56:01,906 --> 01:56:05,364
<i>what my Nonlinear Equations
professor once told me,</i>

1419
01:56:05,910 --> 01:56:09,141
<i>"Always account
for variable change."</i>

1420
01:56:10,949 --> 01:56:12,473
Hello, Micky.

1421
01:56:14,185 --> 01:56:16,016
Look, I got money in Boston.
A hundred grand.

1422
01:56:16,120 --> 01:56:18,145
I'll give it to you.
Just let me walk away. I'll walk away.

1423
01:56:18,256 --> 01:56:21,316
I don't want your money,
Micky. I don't need it.

1424
01:56:27,131 --> 01:56:29,929
But I know someone
who might be interested.

1425
01:56:30,301 --> 01:56:34,397
He's good with numbers, too.
He works for the IRS.

1426
01:56:43,214 --> 01:56:45,273
<i>I let down my good friends.</i>

1427
01:56:45,950 --> 01:56:50,887
<i>But as it turns out, they weren't
too bad at simple math either.</i>

1428
01:57:16,714 --> 01:57:19,274
<i>I scored the prettiest girl
in school.</i>

1429
01:57:22,754 --> 01:57:25,382
<i>I got beaten down
by an old-school Vegas thug</i>

1430
01:57:25,490 --> 01:57:28,687
<i>who was having trouble
accepting his retirement.</i>

1431
01:57:29,994 --> 01:57:33,760
<i>But I worked out a deal with him
that got him a nice pension.</i>

1432
01:57:37,135 --> 01:57:39,933
<i>And... I lied to my mother.</i>

1433
01:57:40,405 --> 01:57:44,102
<i>But I confessed the lie,
and, well, she still loved me.</i>

1434
01:58:00,625 --> 01:58:03,890
<i>So, my senior year of college,
I joined this team.</i>

1435
01:58:04,295 --> 01:58:06,456
<i>And I learned
this new skill.</i>

1436
01:58:06,698 --> 01:58:09,724
<i>I went to Vegas
17 times to use it.</i>

1437
01:58:11,903 --> 01:58:15,430
<i>I made hundreds of thousands
of dollars counting cards.</i>

1438
01:58:16,474 --> 01:58:19,034
And then I had it all stolen from me.

1439
01:58:19,977 --> 01:58:21,137
Twice.

1440
01:58:22,447 --> 01:58:26,543
How's that for life experience,
professor? Did I dazzle you?

1441
01:58:27,719 --> 01:58:30,557
Did I... jump off the page?

